About.jsx
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";

function About() {
    const navigate = useNavigate();

    return (
        <div>
            <h2>About Page</h2>

            <button onClick={() => navigate("/")}>
                Go To Home
            </button>

            <button onClick={() => navigate(-1)}>
                Back
            </button>
        </div>
    );
}

export default About;
Link vs useNavigate

| Feature | Link | useNavigate |
|----------|----------|
| Navigation via UI links | ✅ | ❌ |
| Navigation from JavaScript | ❌ | ✅ |
| Button click navigation | Possible but not preferred | ✅ |
| Login redirect | ❌ | ✅ |
| Logout redirect | ❌ | ✅ |

Interview Questions
What is useNavigate()?

A React Router hook used for programmatic navigation.

How do you navigate to another page?
const navigate = useNavigate();

navigate("/about");
How do you go back?
navigate(-1);
How do you replace history?
navigate("/home", { replace: true });
